<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="397" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1045,1647]" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1513,1539]" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished by the number and arrangement of processes on the aedeagus. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[263,428,1549,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecaloidella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripicta">
<emphasis box="[263,283,1550,1575]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[297,428,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">quadripicta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[481,669,1550,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecaloidella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singaporensis">
<emphasis box="[481,501,1550,1575]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[514,669,1550,1575]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="397">singaporensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but in addition to the aedeagal differences it has the style lateral lobe less produced and the female pregenital sternite with the posterior margin produced medially rather than conically rounded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
